House Rules THIEF CLASS HIGH LEVEL ABILITIES:

-  Level 15: GREATER EVASION
This ability gives -6 to AC and -3 to all saving throws.  In addition, Greater Evasion allows the rogue to move so quickly that his movement rate is increased by 2 and normal missiles have no chance of striking him. Greater Evasion lasts for 5 rounds.

-  Level 20: SET SPIKE TRAP
This ability allows the rogue to set a powerful spring-loaded spike trap that does 20D6 damage to the unsuspecting creature that sets it off.

-  Level 25: ASSASSINATION
Using every clever trick an experienced thief has learned in countless battles, this ability allows every strike in the next round to act as a backstab (or sneak attack), using the thief's existing modifiers to determine damage.

-  Level 30: ASSASSINATION
The rogue gains an additional use of Assassination.
~
@2011 = ~

House Rules BARD CLASS HIGH LEVEL ABILITIES:

-  Level 15: AVOID DEATH
With a superhuman effort, a high-level bard can avoid almost certain death.  The effect lasts for 5 rounds and during this time the bard gains a -5 bonus to save vs. death, his hit points are increased by 20 and the bard becomes immune to death magic for the duration of the ability.

-  Level 20: USE ANY ITEM
Bards take pride in their ability to adapt and make clever use of whatever is at hand.  This ability is an extension of that basic skill.  Once learned, the effect is permanent.  The ability allows the rogue to use any item, even items that are typically restricted to one class.  This
allows the bard to use everything from wands and scrolls to mighty weapons that none but a fighter could otherwise use.

-  Level 25: IMPROVED ALACRITY
Improved Alacrity essentially erases the pause between casting spells.  When active the spellcaster can begin casting a new spell the instant his is finished casting his current spell.  The effect lasts for 2 rounds.

-  Level 30: IMPROVED ALACRITY
The Bard gains an additional use of Improved Alacrity.
~
@2015 = ~

House Rules CLERIC CLASS HIGH LEVEL ABILITIES:

-  Level 15: MASS HEAL
Using divine ability, a high level priest may picture the faces of his fellow party members and focus on the unity of the group.  Upon completion, all party members within 30 foot radius of the caster are healed 2d8 + 2/level hit points.  Other conditions suffered by the party are cured, as well: fatigue, poison, disease, blindness and deafness.

-  Level 20: IMPLOSION
This divine ability creates a rift in the earth beneath the target which implodes and closes in upon itself, crushing and burning the target and holding it for 1 round.  The spell does 10D10 fire damage and 2D10 blunt damage.  The victim can save vs. spell for half damage.

-  Level 25: MASS RAISE DEAD
With divinely-granted control over life or death, a high-level cleric gains a more powerful version of of the Raise Dead Spell.  This ability brings up to 5 party members back to life and heals 3D10-1 per level of the caster points of damage.  They can regain the rest of their hit points by natural healing or curative magic.  This ability restores life to dwarves, gnomes, half-elves, halflings, elves, half-orcs and humans.

-  Level 30: MASS HEAL
The priest gains an additional use of Mass Heal.
~
